%% Diagram: Decision tree for picking a load-balancing algorithm
%% Type: flowchart
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
flowchart TD
    Start([Pick an algorithm])
    Start --> Q1{"Need session affinity<br/>by key — user id,<br/>cache key, tenant?"}

    Q1 -->|Yes| Hash{"Pool size and churn?"}
    Hash -->|Small / stable| Ring["Ring consistent hash<br/>e.g. Ketama, Cassandra vnodes"]
    Hash -->|Large / churny<br/>connection-oriented| Maglev["Maglev hash<br/>e.g. Envoy, Cloudflare Unimog"]

    Q1 -->|No| Q2{"Variable request cost<br/>or backend capacity?"}

    Q2 -->|No, homogeneous| RR["Round robin<br/>weighted RR for capacity tiers"]
    Q2 -->|Yes| Q3{"Pool size?"}

    Q3 -->|Tens of backends| LC["Least connections / least requests<br/>e.g. HAProxy leastconn"]
    Q3 -->|Hundreds+ or<br/>multi-LB pool| P2C["Power of two choices<br/>e.g. Envoy LEAST_REQUEST,<br/>Netflix Zuul Choice-of-2"]
